By Hamza Suleiman Gov. Babagana Zulum of Borno has approved the recruitment of 40 medical doctors of the state origin who studied medicine from various tertiary institutions within and outside Nigeria. Zulum disclosed this when he granted audience to the newly graduated medical doctors in Maiduguri.  He said thatÂ the recruitment was approved as part of the measures to enhance healthcare delivery in the state. According to him, accommodation will be provided to those who are willing to serve in the state.